node.text: The support for last year’s Valor Edition was so incredible that we had to bring back the concept this year. This shoe is extremely special to me because it was inspired by my grandpa who fought in the Korean War and all of my personal proceeds will be donated to the Honor Flight program which takes Veterans to Washington D.C. to visit the monuments and museums and then brings them home to give them a proper Welcome Home. I truly appreciate all of your support, please go to Reebok.com/jjwatt tonight at midnight to pick up your pair.

node.text: We want to change your life, while also helping to change the lives of kids across the country. If you want a chance to win $100,000 and a brand new Ford Raptor, go to Omaze.com/JJ where not only will you have a chance to win, but you'll also be contributing to the Justin J. Watt Foundation and helping support after-school athletics for middle school kids in under-privileged areas! Trust me, this idea is much better than the original idea I had to try and change the world. The video can explain it better than I can...

node.text:
first started training here when I was 15. looked up to the high school kids who started on varsity, dreamt to be like the college athletes who trained in the same gym as me and wondered what it might feel like to be an NFL player like the ones I watched work everyday. 

now we train side by side with the next generation, watching them work, being inspired and pushed by them. All those names and weights on the wall in the back are middle school, high school and college kids, moms and dads, young and old. they’re people who push themselves, put in the work and strive to improve every single day. 

It doesn’t matter what your goal is, just wake up and work for it everyday. Whatever it is. 

#DBWH
